Creating Images with R

with a little bit of magick

Veronica Zuo

My Meme

My meme is about the five stages of grief I went through while doing my assignments and is original because I used a header and stacked it five times.

library(magick)

# header

grief_text <- image_blank(width = 600, 
            height = 200, 
            color = "#333333") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "The Five Stages of Grief",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 40,
                 font = "Calibri",
                 gravity = "center",
                 location = "+0-20") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "(that I went through making this project)", 
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 25,
                 font = "Calibri",
                 gravity = "center",
                 location = "+0+20")

grief_text

# denial photo

denial_image <- image_read("https://www.asaecenter.org/-/media/ASAE/Images/Resources/Articles/AN_Plus/2019/April/tsipursky_how_to_deal_with_a_colleague_in_denial/tsipursky_how_to_deal_with_a_colleague_in_denial_39x22.ashx?h=440&w=780&la=en&hash=6727511BEA6972AFCCDD582B11EB54D070CBE427") %>%
  image_scale(300)
denial_image

# denial text

denial_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                           height = 169, 
                           color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Denial",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Verdana",
                 gravity = "center")
denial_text

# anger!!!

anger_image <- image_read("https://www.churchtimes.co.uk/media/5610493/h4_angry-man.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
anger_image

# anger text

anger_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                          height = 208, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Anger",
               color = "#FFFFFF",
               size = 80,
               font = "Verdana",
               gravity = "center")
anger_text

# bArGaiNinG

bargaining_image <- image_read("https://freedesignfile.com/upload/2017/07/Business-negotiation-Stock-Photo1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
bargaining_image

# bargaining text

bargaining_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                          height = 200, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Bargaining",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Verdana",
                 gravity = "center")
bargaining_text

# depression noooo

depression_image <- image_read("https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit-1500w,f_auto,q_auto:best/newscms/2018_19/2428271/180510-depression-al-1509.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
depression_image

# depression text

depression_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                          height = 169, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Depression",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 58,
                 font = "Verdana",
                 gravity = "center")
depression_text

# acceptance...

acceptance_image <- image_read("https://mytherapynyc.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/zac-durant-_6HzPU9Hyfg-unsplash-1.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)
acceptance_image

# acceptance text 

acceptance_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                          height = 200, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Acceptance",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 55,
                 font = "Verdana",
                 gravity = "center")
acceptance_text

# STACK EM UP!!

first_row <- c(grief_text) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(denial_image, denial_text) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(anger_image, anger_text) %>%
  image_append()

fourth_row <- c(bargaining_image, bargaining_text) %>%
  image_append()

fifth_row <- c(depression_image, depression_text) %>%
  image_append()

sixth_row <- c(acceptance_image, acceptance_text) %>%
  image_append()

grief_vector <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row, fourth_row, fifth_row, sixth_row)

grief <- image_append(grief_vector, stack = TRUE)

#make into image

grief <- image_write(grief, "grief.png")

My Animated GIF

My animated GIF is a person failing to push a wheelbarrow up a plank and falling instead, showing how I felt programming this assignment with many failures, with the looping representing it happened repeatedly. Its originality comes from the frames being specifically selected and paired with text to show progression.

library(magick)

# vector

counts <- 1 : 4 %>% as.character()

# images

frame_05 <- image_read("https://i.postimg.cc/zDwmbCfm/frame-01.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
frame_05

first_fall <- image_read("https://i.postimg.cc/bNY5Z4Mb/frame-02.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
first_fall

last_purple <- image_read("https://i.postimg.cc/wxwCQ6DF/frame-03.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
last_purple

last_frame <- image_read("https://i.postimg.cc/sg7HqyGk/frame-04.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)
last_frame

# frame 1 

frame1 <- frame_05 %>%
  image_annotate(text = "oh", color = "#ffffff", size = 70, font = "Verdana", gravity = "south") %>%
  image_scale(200)
frame1

# frame 2

frame2 <- first_fall %>%
  image_annotate(text = "no", color = "#ffffff", size = 70, font = "Verdana", gravity = "south") %>%
  image_scale(200)
frame2

# frame 3

frame3 <- last_purple %>%
  image_annotate(text = "oh", color = "#ffffff", size = 70, font = "Verdana", gravity = "south") %>%
  image_scale(200)
frame3

# frame 4

frame4 <- last_frame %>%
  image_annotate(text = "yikes!", color = "#ffffff", size = 70, font = "Verdana", gravity = "south") %>%
  image_scale(200)
frame4

# lining it up with a vector

frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# and animate!

frame2 <- image_animate(frames, fps = 2)

# make into gif

frame3 <- image_write(frame2, "frames.gif")
frames
